ZH: 早安！今天天气很好。
EN: Good morning! The weather is great today.

ZH: 早饭吃了吗？
EN: Have you eaten breakfast?

ZH: 他每天早上都去跑步。
EN: He goes jogging every morning.

ZH: 早睡早起身体好。
EN: Early to bed and early to rise makes a man healthy.

ZH: 早点结束工作，我们去看电影吧。
EN: Finish work early and let's go watch a movie.

ZH: 早点儿把作业做完，别拖到最后。
EN: Finish your homework early, don't leave it until the last minute.

ZH: 他跑得太早，影响了比赛结果。
EN: He started running too early and it affected the outcome of the race.

ZH: 早日康复，好好休息。
EN: Get well soon, rest well.

ZH: 早些开始准备，会更顺利的。
EN: Start preparing earlier, it will go smoother.

ZH: 早点洗澡，别冻着了。
EN: Take a shower early, don't catch a cold.

ZH: 早起的鸟儿有虫吃。
EN: The early bird catches the worm.

ZH: 早点回家吧，天要黑了。
EN: Go home early, it's getting dark.

ZH: 他今天早上来上班，但很快就生病了。
EN: He came to work this morning, but soon fell ill.

ZH: 早早地等在门口，等着接他的人。
EN: He waited by the door early, waiting for the person to pick him up.

ZH: 早晨的阳光特别明媚。
EN: The morning sun is especially bright.

ZH: 早点出门，避免堵车。
EN: Leave early to avoid traffic jams.

ZH: 早上的鱼儿最新鲜。
EN: The fish in the morning is the freshest.

ZH: 他早已预料到这个结果。
EN: He had anticipated this outcome long ago.

ZH: 早点休息，别熬夜。
EN: Rest early, don't stay up late.

ZH: 他们太早投降了，没有坚持到底。
EN: They surrendered too early, without persisting to the end.
